KAIZER Chiefs' latest signing Lazarous Kambole says the club's need to win trophies is an ambition he shares. Kambole signed for the Glamour Boys from Zesco United on a three-year deal after previously being linked with Orlando Pirates. Much is expected of the 25-year-old who once scored the fastest ever hat-trick against Mbabane Swallows in the CAF Champions League for Zesco. Speaking of his big ambitions with Chiefs, he told the club's official website: "There were rumours a year ago (about Pirates), but I was patient to move at the right time. This is the right time.       